Introduction
Pipistrelles are the commonest and most widespread of all British bat species. They appear fast and jerky in flight.

Vital statistics
Head & body length: 35mm - 45mm
Forearm length: 29mm - 34mm
Wingspan: 190mm - 230mm
Weight: 3g - 8g
Colour: Medium to dark brown. Face and around the eyes usually pink in
 colour.